        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 2 at 5:33PM MDT until August 2 at 6:15PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>SVRABQ

The National Weather Service in Albuquerque has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Central Union County in northeastern New Mexico...

* Until 615 PM MDT.

* At 533 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 14 miles south of
Mount Dora, or 19 miles southwest of Clayton, moving east at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Ping pong ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect
hail damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles.
Expect wind damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Mainly rural areas of Central Union County.
</description>
        <instruction>Seek shelter inside a well-built structure and stay away from
windows. This storm is capable of producing damaging winds and large
hail.

Motorists can expect brief but sudden changes in visibility and
ponding of water on roadways as storms move through the area.</instruction>
